The paper proposes a framework for instrument segmentation in robot-assisted minimally invasive surgery videos, which involves computer vision, robotics, and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.RO (Robotics) are the most likely categories. The paper also leverages motion flow information and attention network, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG).
